{
  "texts": [
    "Where ⇓h g [X] = {Y ′ ∈ S ′ | ∃X ′ ∈ h g [X]: Y ′ ⊑ ′ X ′ }, let X ′ = int(cl(⇓h g [X])), recalling that int(Y ′) = {Y ′ ∈ S ′ | ∀Z ′ ⊑ ′ Y ′, Z ′ ∈ Y ′ } and cl(Y ′) = {Y ′ ∈ S ′ | ∃Z ′ ⊑ ′ Y ′: Z ′ ∈ Y ′ }.",
    "Then by Fact 2.17.2, X ′ ∈ P ′ f and h g [X] ⊆ h g [S] ∩ X ′.",
    "To show h g [S] ∩ X ′ ⊆ h g [X], suppose X ′ ∈ h g [S] but X ′ ̸ ∈ h g [X].",
    "Since X ′ ∈ h g [S], there is an X ∈ S such that h g (X) = X ′, which with X ′ ̸ ∈ h g [X] implies X ̸ ∈ X.",
    "Then by refinability for X with re- spect to ⊑, there is a Y ⊑ X such that (b) for all Z ⊑ Y, Z ̸ ∈ X."
  ]
}